comment: Specifies all the dependencies from the native OpenSSL engine on an Android KeyStore.

methods.name: private static boolean privateKeySupportsSignature(PrivateKey privateKey, String algorithm)
methods.comment:
* Check if a given PrivateKey object supports a signature algorithm.
     *
     * @param privateKey The PrivateKey handle.
     * @param algorithm The signature algorithm to use.
     * @return whether the algorithm is supported.

methods.name: private static boolean privateKeySupportsCipher(PrivateKey privateKey, String algorithm)
methods.comment:
* Check if a given PrivateKey object supports an encryption algorithm.
     *
     * @param privateKey The PrivateKey handle.
     * @param algorithm The signature algorithm to use.
     * @return whether the algorithm is supported.

methods.name: private static byte[] signWithPrivateKey(PrivateKey privateKey, String algorithm, byte[] message)
methods.comment:
* Sign a given message with a given PrivateKey object.
     *
     * @param privateKey The PrivateKey handle.
     * @param algorithm The signature algorithm to use.
     * @param message The message to sign.
     * @return signature as a byte buffer.

methods.name: private static byte[] encryptWithPrivateKey(PrivateKey privateKey, String algorithm, byte[] message)
methods.comment:
* Encrypts a given input with a given PrivateKey object.
     *
     * @param privateKey The PrivateKey handle.
     * @param algorithm The cipher to use.
     * @param input The input to encrypt.
     * @return ciphertext as a byte buffer.
